00:09:03.470 --> 00:09:09.830
So let's pretend that instead
of the class active learning

00:09:09.830 --> 00:09:13.040
today, I decided I was going
to teach you how to juggle.

00:09:13.040 --> 00:09:17.420
And I said, here's the
equation for how to juggle.

00:09:17.420 --> 00:09:20.300
And here's the variables,
F, D, V N, and H,

00:09:20.300 --> 00:09:22.910
which are ball in the
air, ball in an hand,

00:09:22.910 --> 00:09:26.450
time hand is vacant, number
of balls, number of hands.

00:09:26.450 --> 00:09:28.580
And this is this
handy dandy equation,

00:09:28.580 --> 00:09:32.704
which if you balance it out, it
describes the juggling process.

00:09:32.704 --> 00:09:34.620
And for those of you
that are visual learners,

00:09:34.620 --> 00:09:37.100
I have a graph here, a
yellow ball, a blue ball,

00:09:37.100 --> 00:09:38.390
and a pink ball.

00:09:38.390 --> 00:09:42.680
And then you can see that just
shows the path of the balls.

00:09:42.680 --> 00:09:44.810
If you remember from
physics, there's

00:09:44.810 --> 00:09:49.190
the equations of motion in the
x direction in the y direction.

00:09:49.190 --> 00:09:54.350
And so I think I probably did a
pretty good job of teaching you

00:09:54.350 --> 00:09:54.950
how to juggle.

00:09:59.920 --> 00:10:02.890
No, did a terrible job of
teaching you how to juggle.

00:10:02.890 --> 00:10:05.530
I didn't even come close to
teaching you how to juggle.

00:10:05.530 --> 00:10:07.150
And if I were to
give you a test,

00:10:07.150 --> 00:10:09.550
let's say, and I were to
measure whether or not

00:10:09.550 --> 00:10:13.060
you could juggle, I
guarantee that some of you

00:10:13.060 --> 00:10:15.580
would be able to juggle.

00:10:15.580 --> 00:10:21.310
And I could say, I did a great
job teaching how to juggle.

00:10:21.310 --> 00:10:22.780
But I didn't.

00:10:22.780 --> 00:10:24.580
If you knew how to
juggle coming in,

00:10:24.580 --> 00:10:26.320
presumably you still
know how to juggle.

00:10:26.320 --> 00:10:28.990
I did no harm, I think.

00:10:28.990 --> 00:10:31.665
However if you didn't know
how to juggle coming in,

00:10:31.665 --> 00:10:33.040
you don't know
how to juggle now.

00:10:36.390 --> 00:10:38.040
So why is this here now?

00:10:38.040 --> 00:10:40.605
Why did I bother to
do this stupid thought

00:10:40.605 --> 00:10:41.480
experiment right now?

00:10:48.735 --> 00:10:50.110
AUDIENCE: Because
this is clearly

00:10:50.110 --> 00:10:52.939
how most classes are taught.

00:10:52.939 --> 00:10:54.730
Obviously it would be
easier to have a ball

00:10:54.730 --> 00:10:56.969
and show us how to juggle,
active learning as opposed

00:10:56.969 --> 00:11:00.894
to just showing the theory
behind it and ending there.

00:11:00.894 --> 00:11:02.560
JANET RANKIN: And I
think a lot of times

00:11:02.560 --> 00:11:05.830
we really do, in science and
engineering classes, we really

00:11:05.830 --> 00:11:07.720
put up a lot of equations.

00:11:07.720 --> 00:11:09.490
And then it's not like
we expect somebody

00:11:09.490 --> 00:11:12.474
to do something
physically with them.

00:11:12.474 --> 00:11:14.890
But we expect them to be able
to manipulate the equations,

00:11:14.890 --> 00:11:17.680
transfer the equations,
apply the equations.

00:11:17.680 --> 00:11:20.740
And we never really
talked about that.

00:11:20.740 --> 00:11:24.500
We talked about the equations.

00:11:24.500 --> 00:11:28.460
So it's a real call
in my mind, for us

00:11:28.460 --> 00:11:29.990
to think about what
it is we really

00:11:29.990 --> 00:11:32.070
want students to be able to do.

00:11:32.070 --> 00:11:34.040
And then make sure that
they're doing stuff

00:11:34.040 --> 00:11:38.760
to teach them that helps
them learn how to do that.

00:11:38.760 --> 00:11:42.300
And I know you all
read the readings

00:11:42.300 --> 00:11:45.040
and that they talk a lot
about active learning.

00:11:45.040 --> 00:11:47.710
There's a few things about
techniques for active learning.

00:11:47.710 --> 00:11:50.043
There's a few things about
the why's of active learning.

00:11:50.043 --> 00:11:53.310
There's some data for why
active learning works.

00:11:53.310 --> 00:11:56.100
But I'm guessing that
there's a range of buy in

00:11:56.100 --> 00:11:58.170
